    'Prime Rib Roast with Au Jus': `<h2>Prime Rib Roast with Au Jus</h2><h3>Ingredients</h3><table><colgroup><col style="width: 52%"/><col style="width: 15%"/><col style="width: 15%"/><col style="width: 15%"/></colgroup><thead><tr class="header"><th>Ingredient</th><th>50</th><th>100</th><th>140</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr class="odd"><td>Prime rib roast, bone-in</td><td>50 lb</td><td>100 lb</td><td>140 lb</td></tr><tr class="even"><td>Kosher salt &amp; pepper</td><td>to taste</td><td>to taste</td><td>to taste</td></tr><tr class="odd"><td>Olive oil</td><td>1 qt</td><td>2 qt</td><td>2.8 qt</td></tr><tr class="even"><td>Garlic, minced</td><td>6 oz</td><td>12 oz</td><td>17 oz</td></tr><tr class="odd"><td>Fresh rosemary, chopped</td><td>½ cup</td><td>1 cup</td><td>1.4 cup</td></tr><tr class="even"><td>Beef stock (for au jus)</td><td>8 qt</td><td>16 qt</td><td>22 qt</td></tr><tr class="odd"><td>Red wine (optional, for jus)</td><td>2 qt</td><td>4 qt</td><td>5.5 qt</td></tr></tbody></table><h3>Method</h3><ol type="1"><li><p>Season roast with salt, pepper, garlic, rosemary, andoil.</p></li><li><p>Roast at 325°F until internal temp 130–135°F for medium-rare(~1.5–2 hr).</p></li><li><p>Rest 20 min; slice.</p></li><li><p>Make au jus by deglazing roasting pan with stock and wine; reduceslightly.</p></li></ol><p>Holding</p>` ,
    'Stuffed Cornish Hen with Herbed Bread Filling': `<h2>Stuffed Cornish Hen with Herbed Bread Filling</h2><h3>Ingredients</h3><table><colgroup><col style="width: 55%"/><col style="width: 14%"/><col style="width: 14%"/><col style="width: 15%"/></colgroup><thead><tr class="header"><th>Ingredient</th><th>50</th><th>100</th><th>140</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr class="odd"><td>Cornish hens, 6–8 oz portions</td><td>50 ea</td><td>100 ea</td><td>140 ea</td></tr><tr class="even"><td>Olive oil or butter</td><td>1 qt</td><td>2 qt</td><td>2.8 qt</td></tr><tr class="odd"><td>Kosher salt &amp; pepper</td><td>to taste</td><td>to taste</td><td>to taste</td></tr><tr class="even"><td>Bread cubes</td><td>6 lb</td><td>12 lb</td><td>17 lb</td></tr><tr class="odd"><td>Onion, diced</td><td>3 lb</td><td>6 lb</td><td>8.5 lb</td></tr><tr class="even"><td>Celery, diced</td><td>3 lb</td><td>6 lb</td><td>8.5 lb</td></tr><tr class="odd"><td>Garlic, minced</td><td>4 oz</td><td>8 oz</td><td>11 oz</td></tr><tr class="even"><td>Fresh parsley, chopped</td><td>½ cup</td><td>1 cup</td><td>1.4 cup</td></tr><tr class="odd"><td>Fresh thyme</td><td>¼ cup</td><td>½ cup</td><td>¾ cup</td></tr><tr class="even"><td>Chicken stock</td><td>2 qt</td><td>4 qt</td><td>5.5 qt</td></tr></tbody></table><h3>Method</h3><ol type="1"><li><p>Sauté onion, celery, garlic in oil or butter; combine with breadcubes, herbs, and stock to moisten.</p></li><li><p>Stuff hens; truss if necessary.</p></li><li><p>Roast at 375°F until internal temp 165°F (~40–50 min).</p></li></ol><p>Holding</p>` ,
    'Butternut Squash & Chestnut Lasagna (V)': `<h2>Butternut Squash & Chestnut Lasagna (V)</h2><h3>Ingredients</h3><table><colgroup><col style="width: 60%"/><col style="width: 13%"/><col style="width: 13%"/><col style="width: 13%"/></colgroup><thead><tr class="header"><th>Ingredient</th><th>50</th><th>100</th><th>140</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr class="odd"><td>Lasagna noodles, uncooked</td><td>10 lb</td><td>20 lb</td><td>28 lb</td></tr><tr class="even"><td>Butternut squash, roasted &amp; mashed</td><td>12 lb</td><td>24 lb</td><td>34 lb</td></tr><tr class="odd"><td>Chestnuts, cooked &amp; chopped</td><td>4 lb</td><td>8 lb</td><td>11 lb</td></tr><tr class="even"><td>Ricotta cheese</td><td>6 lb</td><td>12 lb</td><td>17 lb</td></tr><tr class="odd"><td>Parmesan cheese, grated</td><td>4 lb</td><td>8 lb</td><td>11 lb</td></tr><tr class="even"><td>Mozzarella cheese, shredded</td><td>6 lb</td><td>12 lb</td><td>17 lb</td></tr><tr class="odd"><td>Egg</td><td>25 ea</td><td>50 ea</td><td>70 ea</td></tr><tr class="even"><td>Nutmeg, grated</td><td>2 tsp</td><td>4 tsp</td><td>6 tsp</td></tr><tr class="odd"><td>Kosher salt &amp; pepper</td><td>to taste</td><td>to taste</td><td>to taste</td></tr><tr class="even"><td>Béchamel sauce</td><td>6 qt</td><td>12 qt</td><td>17 qt</td></tr></tbody></table><h3>Method</h3><ol type="1"><li><p>Mix ricotta, egg, nutmeg, salt, and pepper.</p></li><li><p>Layer noodles, squash, chestnuts, ricotta, mozzarella, andbéchamel in pans.</p></li><li><p>Top with Parmesan; bake at 375°F until bubbly and golden (~35–40min).</p></li></ol><p>Holding</p>` ,
